Pre-Game Insights: Team Netherlands and Namibia will face each other in match five of the first-round encounters of the 2022 T20 World Cup.
The match will be played at the Simonds Stadium, Geelong on October 18 (Tuesday).
This will be both teams’ second match in the tournament.
Namibia will take on Sri Lanka in its tournament opener, while the Netherlands will face UAE in their first encounter on the same day.
Namibia won their last meeting against the Netherlands in the 2021 T20 World Cup by six wickets with one over to spare.
The Dutch side holds the edge in overall T20I records after winning two games against Namibia.
Namibia has also registered a T20I victory against the Dutch side in a quadrangular series in 2013.
